Label: digestible carbohydrate
Text definition: Also known as available {carbohydrate} corresponds to fractions of total carbohydrate that is digestible to provide energy.

Label: non digestible carbohydrate
Text definition: {carbohydrate} components which are not easily digestible, and form major part of dietary fibre (TDF)

Label: seed carbohydrate concentration
Equivalent to:
PATO:'concentration of' and 
'inheres in' some ('seed' and
'towards' some 'carbohydrate')

Label: free sugar
Text definition: Mono-, di-, or oligosaccharides that are naturally occur freely, not bound or part of larger polysaccharides

Label: seed protein concentration
Equivalent to:
PATO:'concentration of' and 
'inheres in' some ('seed' and
'towards' some 'protein')
